-What?

777
00:57:44,171 --> 00:57:45,214
I'm so cold.

778
00:57:55,224 --> 00:57:56,475
I'm cold.

779
00:58:00,062 --> 00:58:01,605
My hands are freezing.

780
00:58:02,272 --> 00:58:03,273
I'm so cold.

781
00:58:09,029 --> 00:58:11,406
How could you push me off
the cliff and leave me?

782
00:58:11,490 --> 00:58:13,450
I'm still here.

783
00:58:20,582 --> 00:58:21,458
How…

784
00:58:22,793 --> 00:58:25,546
-How could my brother…
-I'm cold.

785
00:58:28,006 --> 00:58:30,467
Jeong-bae, help me up already.

786
00:58:31,635 --> 00:58:33,679
It's freezing down here. Okay?

787
00:58:34,346 --> 00:58:36,682
-I'm so cold, Jeong-bae.
-Go away.

788
00:58:36,765 --> 00:58:39,184
-Get away from me.
-Jeong-bae.

789
00:58:39,268 --> 00:58:41,979
-Get off me.
-Jeong-bae.

790
00:58:43,272 --> 00:58:45,732
Jeong-bae.

791
00:58:45,816 --> 00:58:47,025
-Let go.
-Jeong-bae.

792
00:58:47,109 --> 00:58:49,319
-No!
-Jeong-bae.

793
00:58:49,403 --> 00:58:50,946
-Go away.
-I'm cold, Jeong-bae.

794
00:58:51,029 --> 00:58:54,199
Jeong-bae, I'm so cold.

795
00:58:54,283 --> 00:58:56,034
Get away from me!

796
00:58:56,118 --> 00:58:58,078
Jeong-bae, I'm so cold.

797
00:59:02,874 --> 00:59:04,126
Why are there

798
00:59:05,586 --> 00:59:08,630
so many burdens in my life?

799
00:59:10,465 --> 00:59:13,844
It's not that you have many burdens.
You are just weak.

800
00:59:15,262 --> 00:59:17,472
The weaker you are,

801
00:59:18,348 --> 00:59:21,101
the heavier your burdens become.

802
00:59:22,269 --> 00:59:23,478
I see.

803
00:59:24,354 --> 00:59:28,066
Do you want to see
what will kill you eventually?

804
00:59:29,651 --> 00:59:31,820
Yes. I do.

805
01:00:09,775 --> 01:00:11,610
BABEL

806
01:00:21,620 --> 01:00:25,374
Unless you cut ties with Babel,
you will die a miserable death.

807
01:00:29,503 --> 01:00:30,921
Is that all I need to do?

808
01:00:35,592 --> 01:00:37,803
It's more than cutting ties with them.

809
01:00:39,179 --> 01:00:42,808
You must cut ties with them
as you completely trample on them.

810
01:00:42,891 --> 01:00:44,101
What?

811
01:00:44,184 --> 01:00:45,727
To get rid of bad luck altogether.

812
01:00:47,771 --> 01:00:48,772
That's…

813
01:00:49,439 --> 01:00:52,109
It's not that easy.

814
01:01:08,959 --> 01:01:10,460
I see.

815
01:01:14,005 --> 01:01:15,841
That's the number of days you have left.

816
01:01:17,175 --> 01:01:18,093
Five days.

817
01:01:27,352 --> 01:01:29,187
Poor thing.

818
01:01:40,866 --> 01:01:41,950
You know what?

819
01:01:42,701 --> 01:01:46,329
I went too hard earlier.
My arms are hurting. They hurt so much.

820
01:01:49,541 --> 01:01:51,501
Isn't it ironic?

821
01:01:51,585 --> 01:01:55,255
A newspaper company is supposed to
publish facts, but he's so superstitious.

822
01:01:56,423 --> 01:02:00,093
He's superstitious
because he has no interest in facts.

823
01:02:04,347 --> 01:02:05,515
You startled me.

824
01:02:05,599 --> 01:02:06,516
Oh, right.

825
01:02:06,600 --> 01:02:10,854
I forgot to tell you
because we were so busy today.

826
01:02:10,937 --> 01:02:14,274
I found something shocking about
Jang Han-seok in the Guillotine file.

827
01:02:15,025 --> 01:02:16,818
-What is it?
-Chairman Jang

828
01:02:17,569 --> 01:02:20,238
killed four of his classmates
in middle and high school.

829
01:02:22,699 --> 01:02:26,578
He brought classmates he didn't like
to a rooftop and made them jump.

830
01:02:26,661 --> 01:02:29,790
Or he hunted and killed them
in the mountains like they were prey.

831
01:02:30,874 --> 01:02:35,796
He killed the last one because he stole
a ball from him during a gym class.

832
01:02:36,379 --> 01:02:39,549
Jang used the goal net to strangle him.

833
01:02:41,843 --> 01:02:43,428
Here's what's scarier.

834
01:02:59,361 --> 01:03:00,529
JANG HAN-SEOK

835
01:03:27,472 --> 01:03:29,391
He took the deceased's watches

836
01:03:29,474 --> 01:03:31,977
as some kind of a trophy.

837
01:03:32,894 --> 01:03:36,606
And he even bragged about it
like he was proud of it.

838
01:03:38,316 --> 01:03:39,943
He's a psychopath.

839
01:03:40,026 --> 01:03:42,946
He was diagnosed as a psychopath
at the age of 16.

840
01:03:43,029 --> 01:03:46,408
That's why his father sent him
to the States

841
01:03:46,491 --> 01:03:48,869
fearing that he might become
a serial killer.

842
01:03:48,952 --> 01:03:51,955
Jang Han-seo was beaten
and tortured by him,

843
01:03:52,038 --> 01:03:55,292
so he's been seeing a therapist
ever since he was little.

844
01:03:55,375 --> 01:03:57,836
And that's how he ended up doing drugs.

845
01:03:57,919 --> 01:04:00,171
Even so, he shouldn't be doing drugs.

846
01:04:00,255 --> 01:04:01,756
That jerk.

847
01:04:01,840 --> 01:04:03,592
Anyway, their father, Jang Guk-hwan,

848
01:04:04,259 --> 01:04:06,177
covered everything up with money

849
01:04:06,887 --> 01:04:07,971
and kept it a secret.

850
01:04:11,975 --> 01:04:14,352
That explains why he was so hard to beat.

851
01:04:16,021 --> 01:04:17,272
Turns out he's

852
01:04:18,648 --> 01:04:20,108
the biggest monster of them all.

853
01:04:28,825 --> 01:04:31,453
BABEL SUSPECTED TO HAVE MADE
FALSE STATEMENTS TO RAISE STOCK VALUE

854
01:04:50,096 --> 01:04:51,264
DAECHANG DAILY

855
01:04:53,558 --> 01:04:54,559
Hello?

856
01:04:54,643 --> 01:04:56,019
What are you doing?

857
01:04:56,853 --> 01:04:59,064
-What the hell is this?
-Mr. Jang.

858
01:04:59,147 --> 01:05:04,069
There has been a change
in the guidelines at my company.

859
01:05:04,945 --> 01:05:07,030
Did I do something to offend you?

860
01:05:07,113 --> 01:05:09,032
No, you didn't.

861
01:05:09,115 --> 01:05:13,703
Now Daechang Daily is an honest newspaper
that only speaks the truth.

862
01:05:13,787 --> 01:05:14,746
The truth?

863
01:05:15,330 --> 01:05:18,750
You're the most corrupt newspaper company
in Korea. But what? The truth?

864
01:05:18,833 --> 01:05:20,585
Watch what you say.

865
01:05:20,669 --> 01:05:22,796
So, why didn't you
run your company properly?

866
01:05:23,296 --> 01:05:24,464
I'm hanging up.

867
01:05:24,547 --> 01:05:26,216
Mr. Oh? Mr. Oh!

868
01:05:26,800 --> 01:05:27,676
Hey!

869
01:05:43,024 --> 01:05:46,569
How come my days are still numbered?

870
01:05:46,653 --> 01:05:49,823
I just cut all ties with Babel.

871
01:05:49,906 --> 01:05:52,617
That won't be enough to save your life.

872
01:05:52,701 --> 01:05:53,910
Pardon?

873
01:05:54,869 --> 01:05:59,416
Then what more do I need to do?

874
01:06:01,459 --> 01:06:03,586
The owner of Babel.

875
01:06:03,670 --> 01:06:04,713
The king of Babel.

876
01:06:10,051 --> 01:06:11,344
Are you talking about

877
01:06:11,428 --> 01:06:14,055
Chairman Jang Han-seok?

878
01:06:15,432 --> 01:06:17,684
He's the one
who's holding onto your misfortune.

879
01:06:19,269 --> 01:06:22,272
If you expose his past evils,

880
01:06:22,355 --> 01:06:25,734
and relieve the spirits that wander
the realm of the living because of him,

881
01:06:26,484 --> 01:06:29,487
those spirits will help you.

882
01:06:37,662 --> 01:06:40,206
The wandering spirits?

883
01:06:46,629 --> 01:06:49,883
Are you saying Han-seok killed someone?

884
01:07:14,199 --> 01:07:15,366
Han-seok.

885
01:07:16,868 --> 01:07:18,578
I'm sorry.

886
01:07:18,661 --> 01:07:20,371
Don't hit me.

887
01:07:20,455 --> 01:07:24,042
Han-seok. I'm sorry.

888
01:07:24,125 --> 01:07:25,293
It's all my fault.

889
01:07:25,376 --> 01:07:26,961
-I'm not Han-seok.
-I'm sorry.

890
01:07:27,045 --> 01:07:28,505
-I'm not him.
-Don't strangle me.

891
01:07:28,588 --> 01:07:30,548
-I can't breathe.
-Jang Han-seok.

892
01:07:30,632 --> 01:07:31,674
Don't strangle me.

893
01:07:31,758 --> 01:07:33,510
-Jang Han-seok. Spare me.
-No.

894
01:07:33,593 --> 01:07:35,178
-It's my fault.
-Don't do it.

895
01:07:35,261 --> 01:07:37,388
No. I'm not Han-seok!

896
01:07:37,472 --> 01:07:38,723
That's my watch.

897
01:07:38,807 --> 01:07:41,392
That's my watch. It's mine.

898
01:07:41,476 --> 01:07:43,937
-It's my watch.
-No.

899
01:07:45,772 --> 01:07:50,151
The chairman of Babel,
one of the biggest companies in Korea,

900
01:07:50,235 --> 01:07:51,611
was a bully?

901
01:07:51,694 --> 01:07:54,114
No. It was more of a massacre.

902
01:07:54,697 --> 01:07:57,784
This has come
as shocking news to the public.

903
01:07:57,867 --> 01:08:00,995
On top of that,
he was never punished for his crimes,

904
01:08:01,079 --> 01:08:04,749
and was able to climb the ladder
to become the chairman.

905
01:08:05,375 --> 01:08:07,919
I mean, seriously?
Where were the police and prosecutors

906
01:08:08,002 --> 01:08:09,921
in all of this?

907
01:08:10,630 --> 01:08:12,382
Right now, a lot of people

908
01:08:12,465 --> 01:08:15,468
are urging this killer chairman
to be punished

909
01:08:15,552 --> 01:08:18,429
on many of the online forums
and petitioning for it as well.

910
01:08:19,013 --> 01:08:20,306
Gosh.

911
01:08:21,432 --> 01:08:23,351
How did they know?

912
01:08:23,434 --> 01:08:27,564
Even Mr. Oh wouldn't
know about my childhood.

913
01:08:27,647 --> 01:08:30,191
…update you with a follow-up coverage.

914
01:08:30,275 --> 01:08:31,818
Right now, Babel Group

915
01:08:31,901 --> 01:08:33,736
-has dismissed the claims
-Hey.

916
01:08:33,820 --> 01:08:35,405
-It wasn't you, right?
-as being false.

917
01:08:35,488 --> 01:08:38,700
-They will soon release
-What? Of course, it wasn't me.

918
01:08:38,783 --> 01:08:42,328
The article even said I was crazy
and did drugs. You think I did that?

919
01:08:44,080 --> 01:08:45,415
Well, you're right.

920
01:08:48,168 --> 01:08:52,672
It was reported that there hadn't been
an investigation on this in the past.

921
01:08:54,174 --> 01:08:56,676
Who else knows about this?

922
01:08:58,553 --> 01:09:01,973
My dad, the detective who worked the case,

923
01:09:02,557 --> 01:09:03,975
and the prosecutor in charge.

924
01:09:06,477 --> 01:09:10,398
Then there's a source we're not aware of.

925
01:09:11,149 --> 01:09:14,819
The problem is the intention.
Why is Mr. Oh attacking you now?

926
01:09:15,403 --> 01:09:17,822
It looks like
he's trying to bring me down.

927
01:09:34,380 --> 01:09:38,301
LIFE

928
01:09:51,147 --> 01:09:52,815
It's all done.

929
01:09:53,566 --> 01:09:55,026
You have been spared.

930
01:10:01,574 --> 01:10:04,285
Fate has a weakness for brave souls,

931
01:10:04,827 --> 01:10:07,121
but it can be a powerful foe
to those who are weak.

932
01:10:09,082 --> 01:10:11,834
You have been brave
and averted this crisis.

933
01:10:43,199 --> 01:10:45,618
Thank you.

934
01:10:46,869 --> 01:10:49,247
Thank you.

935
01:11:11,477 --> 01:11:12,895
It's been a while, Mr. Cho.

936
01:11:12,979 --> 01:11:14,480
Can we meet now?

937
01:11:14,564 --> 01:11:16,858
I'll meet you at the parking lot
of the plaza.

938
01:11:17,984 --> 01:11:19,986
Okay. Sure.

939
01:11:20,987 --> 01:11:21,904
Okay.

940
01:12:47,740 --> 01:12:48,741
Run!

941
01:12:55,873 --> 01:12:57,250
Who are they?

942
01:12:57,875 --> 01:13:00,837
I think Prosecutor Jung sent them.

943
01:13:02,672 --> 01:13:03,714
Prosecutor Jung?

944
01:13:07,468 --> 01:13:09,345
It's as expected.

945
01:13:09,429 --> 01:13:11,681
It was Vincenzo.

946
01:13:11,764 --> 01:13:14,934
He exploited Mr. Oh's tendency
to have blind faith in shamans.

947
01:13:15,601 --> 01:13:17,311
He's so detailed.

948
01:13:19,021 --> 01:13:21,357
I really can't beat a Mafia member.

949
01:13:23,151 --> 01:13:24,485
Anyway…

950
01:13:24,569 --> 01:13:28,239
how did he find out
what happened when I was young?

951
01:13:28,906 --> 01:13:31,242
That's still a mystery to me.

952
01:13:31,325 --> 01:13:34,996
But it's most likely that he got it
from the intelligence agency.

953
01:13:37,165 --> 01:13:39,792
How on earth did he find out?

954
01:13:40,376 --> 01:13:42,462
Given the current circumstances,

955
01:13:42,545 --> 01:13:45,673
he's pitted Babel and Daechang
against each other.

956
01:13:45,756 --> 01:13:49,510
Even so. Mr. Oh of all people
can't do that to me.

957
01:13:50,887 --> 01:13:51,971
What should we do?

958
01:13:56,017 --> 01:13:59,979
Make Vincenzo end it himself.

959
01:14:00,062 --> 01:14:02,607
Oh, right. I must show you something.

960
01:14:06,235 --> 01:14:07,153
What is it?

961
01:14:08,654 --> 01:14:11,157
Vincenzo's Korean name is Park Ju-hyeong.

962
01:14:11,240 --> 01:14:14,368
He was adopted after being abandoned
by his mother when he was little.

963
01:14:14,452 --> 01:14:15,703
OH GYEONG-JA, PERSONAL DETAILS

964
01:14:15,786 --> 01:14:16,996
Is his mom alive?

965
01:14:17,079 --> 01:14:19,999
She is. But she recently got out of prison

966
01:14:20,082 --> 01:14:22,418
-because of pancreatic cancer.
-What was she in for?

967
01:14:22,502 --> 01:14:24,921
She was the housekeeper
who was involved in the death

968
01:14:25,004 --> 01:14:27,465
of Shinkwang Finance's Chairman Hwang.

969
01:14:28,925 --> 01:14:30,092
NAMDONGBU DISTRICT COURT
RULING

970
01:14:30,176 --> 01:14:31,052
Wait.

971
01:14:31,552 --> 01:14:34,430
He ruined the signing ceremony
a while ago.

972
01:14:37,767 --> 01:14:39,560
Is this why he did that?

973
01:14:39,644 --> 01:14:40,686
Yes.

974
01:14:41,687 --> 01:14:44,899
Hong Yu-chan was the public defender
who took her case.

975
01:14:44,982 --> 01:14:49,529
And today, she filed for a retrial
regarding the death of Hwang Deok-bae.

976
01:14:49,612 --> 01:14:50,780
A retrial?

977
01:14:52,782 --> 01:14:54,909
-Who filed it?
-Cha-young did.

978
01:14:54,992 --> 01:14:57,370
Of course, Vincenzo must be behind it.

979
01:15:03,292 --> 01:15:06,379
That means Vincenzo
has been spending time with his mother.

980
01:15:06,462 --> 01:15:11,259
I'm trying to find out which hospital
his mother is being treated in.

981
01:15:18,099 --> 01:15:21,561
I met Jung at the International Security
Intelligence Service five years ago.

982
01:15:22,311 --> 01:15:25,565
He was dispatched for a case,
and I had a desk job there.

983
01:15:26,315 --> 01:15:28,818
We found out the true nature
of the Guillotine file,

984
01:15:28,901 --> 01:15:30,236
and Jung thought he could

985
01:15:30,319 --> 01:15:33,364
root out all corruption in Korea
with the file.

986
01:15:33,948 --> 01:15:36,242
So he desperately tried
to get his hands on it,

987
01:15:36,325 --> 01:15:38,369
and I joined hands with him.

988
01:15:39,662 --> 01:15:41,747
That was before he went dirty.

989
01:15:41,831 --> 01:15:42,790
Yes.

990
01:15:43,749 --> 01:15:46,127
But soon,
the file was hacked and vanished,

991
01:15:46,210 --> 01:15:48,504
and I volunteered to look for the file.

992
01:15:49,880 --> 01:15:51,507
That's how I got here.

993
01:15:52,675 --> 01:15:55,636
But Jung has betrayed you, right?

994
01:15:56,304 --> 01:16:00,433
Yes. In fact, I suspected him
these past few months.

995
01:16:01,017 --> 01:16:04,437
I felt he had an ulterior motive
for looking for the file.

996
01:16:07,189 --> 01:16:10,526
Now that he is on Jang Han-seok's side,
he must know by now

997
01:16:11,319 --> 01:16:14,780
that the file and the gold are here.

998
01:16:14,864 --> 01:16:19,118
And he must know he has to demolish
the plaza to retrieve them.

999
01:16:27,168 --> 01:16:28,711
GEUMGA PLAZA

1000
01:17:00,701 --> 01:17:03,120
PETITION FOR A RETRIAL

1001
01:18:07,810 --> 01:18:08,769
Damn it.

1002
01:19:41,904 --> 01:19:43,364
Mr. Vincenzo Cassano.

1003
01:19:43,447 --> 01:19:46,325
You're under arrest
for the murder of Oh Jeong-bae.

1004
01:20:21,277 --> 01:20:23,028
SPECIAL THANKS TO LEE HYE-JUNG
AND IM SUNG-JAE

1005
01:20:51,724 --> 01:20:53,142
It was a setup, wasn't it?

1006
01:20:53,851 --> 01:20:56,228
Then we'll have to use
the most effective method.

1007
01:20:56,312 --> 01:20:57,521
I'll make sure no one ever gets it.

1008
01:20:57,605 --> 01:20:59,356
I have to find the person who lured me.

1009
01:20:59,440 --> 01:21:02,151
I'll make sure everyone who tried to
build it will be punished.

1010
01:21:02,234 --> 01:21:05,988
He could stir up the entire nation.

1011
01:21:07,239 --> 01:21:10,117
To cherish Geumga Plaza
as a historical building.

1012
01:21:11,076 --> 01:21:12,870
Make him pay.

1013
01:21:14,121 --> 01:21:15,581
It's time for you to die.

1014
01:21:15,664 --> 01:21:19,585
You will die a slow death,
experiencing it every step of the way.

1015
01:21:21,337 --> 01:21:26,342
Subtitle translation by: Won-hyang Son
